Cook sausage in a large skillet over medium high heat for 3 minutes, turning occasionally. Remove sausage and set aside. Add oil and potatoes to skillet and cook until golden brown. Add ale, sauerkraut and mustard to skillet, mixing with potatoes until blended. Cook over medium-high heat for 2 minutes. Return the sausage to the skillet, continue cooking for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.